This paper analyzes online collective evaluation processes in social media, which involves analyzing user-generated content and evaluating it through positive and negative votes. This topic falls under the sub-category of social media analysis (cs.SI) as well as social computing (cs.SOC). The paper also discusses the role of emotions expressed through text, which falls under natural language processing (cs.CL) and cyberpsychology (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper touches on the spread of information and polarization, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
